<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-1580] Reject producer requests to internal topics</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1580</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Producer requests to internal topics (currently only __consumer_offset) can be disastrous.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;E.g., if we allow a message to be appended to the offsets topic this could lead to fatal exceptions when loading the offsets topic and when compacting the log.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Producer requests to these topics should be rejected.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
